 <a name="career"></a>
<h3>CLAS Career Advising</h3>
<div class="listing">
<a href="https://www.advising.ufl.edu/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/andreamcochran.jpg"><img src="https://www.advising.ufl.edu/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/andreamcochran.jpg" alt="Andie Cochran" width="100" height="134" class="staff" /></a>
<h3>Andie Cochran<br />
Associate Director for the Career and Industry Engagement<br />Email: andreamcochran@ufl.edu</h3>

<p>I am an extension of the Career Connection Center that works with students, faculty and staff from the College of Liberal Arts and Sciences, as well as connects employers to CLAS. I meet with students one on one, facilitate workshops, work with faculty and staff to bring CRC services to students and work with employers that are eager to recruit Liberal Arts and Sciences students. As a former Liberal Arts and Sciences undergrad, I was able to translate my Psychology degree into a career in the hospitality industry that allowed me to use a variety of transferrable skills. I am able to bring this knowledge to my role at the UF Career Connection Center with the hope to share it with students in order to guide and motivate their career exploration.</p>
</div>






